DATA CLOUD
Data Cloud Permission Set Names During the Enhanced Security Migration Period

Starting in November 2023, the existing Data Cloud standard permission sets were renamed and new permission sets with similar names were created in every Data Cloud org. Refer to these tables to understand the new names for existing permission sets and names of equivalent new permission sets.

NOTE The Data Cloud Admin and Data Cloud Marketing Admin standard permission sets are compatible with both legacy or enhanced security data spaces because they permit admins to view features and feature setup across all data spaces. However, you must associate data spaces with the admin permission sets to give admins access to data within the data spaces.
Permission Sets for Data Cloud Orgs with Customer Data Platform Licenses
ORIGINAL NAME OF EXISTING DATA CLOUD STANDARD PERMISSION SET	NEW NAME FOR EXISTING PERMISSION SET	EQUIVALENT ENHANCED SECURITY STANDARD PERMISSION SET
Data Cloud Data Aware Specialist	(Legacy) Data Cloud Data Award Specialist	Data Cloud Data Aware Specialist
Data Cloud Marketing Manager	(Legacy) Data Cloud Marketing Manager	Data Cloud Marketing Manager
Data Cloud Marketing Specialist	(Legacy) Data Cloud Marketing Specialist	Data Cloud Marketing Specialist
Permission Sets for Data Cloud Orgs with Data Cloud Licenses
ORIGINAL NAME OF EXISTING DATA CLOUD STANDARD PERMISSION SET	NEW NAME FOR EXISTING PERMISSION SET	EQUIVALENT ENHANCED SECURITY STANDARD PERMISSION SET
Data Cloud User	(Legacy) Data Cloud User	Data Cloud User
Data Cloud for Marketing Data Aware Specialist	(Legacy) Data Cloud for Marketing Data Aware Specialist	Data Cloud Data Aware Specialist
Data Cloud for Marketing Manager	(Legacy) Data Cloud for Marketing Manager	Data Cloud Marketing Manager
Data Cloud for Marketing Specialist	(Legacy) Data Cloud for Marketing Specialist	Data Cloud Marketing Specialist
